Write a new post CHAO BBS  


Dying chao... 
 


Pepero ID:003266 2001/12/20 00:00:08   Reply  Edit post  Homepage  
 &lt;pepero@rcn.com&gt;

In my experience when they cocoon and then fade to nothing, if you just stand there.. they are gone. If I have one I really like I keep an update of it in daycare. I have tried other ways also...
1. Shut off Dreamcast... do not SAVE, reload. Go back to daycare.
a. he may be sleeping and you can pick him up and put in VMU.
b. he may be in cocoon but visible... you can run in and race him at the track if your in neutral garden... if he's anygood, leave race, RUSH through garden, go to daycare on the net and save for further modification / or not.
c. you may find an egg (name gone, probably not any relationship)
d. you may find two eggs, usually one has your chao's name.
e. you may get a reset garden with two fresh eggs and no chao, trees, toys etc. 

I usually play it safe and leave the garden as soon as I suspect he's dying then post him on the daycare. YES! HE WILL SHOW AS LIVE CHAO IN DAYCARE. he will be on a &quot;hair trigger&quot; to die and must be treated VERY SPECIAL when dowloaded. You can race him from your download file and never take him out or you can modify him. If you want my experience email me.  
 

CHAO BBS After submitting a new post, reload the page.  

